"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-01-30-french-rights-body-probe-paris-homeless-clean-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - France's top State human rights body said yesterday that it would probe criticism of efforts to relocate the city's homeless population ahead of the Paris Olympics this year.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9992042311392761, \"rank\": 0.0006227485858531268, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 22, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9992042311392761, \"rank\": 0.0006227485858531268, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some charities have accused local authorities of carrying out a \\\"social cleansing\\\" operation in the capital region, ahead of the Games, by clearing away the homeless as well as migrant camps and slums.\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The transfer of people from Paris to temporary accommodation centres in provincial France has caused tensions and demonstrations in some towns and rural areas.\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 429, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998954233488, \"rank\": 1.0457676216703239e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9992042311392761, \"rank\": 0.0006227485858531268, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French rights ombudswoman Claire Hedon said she had started an investigation into \\\"the threat to rights and freedoms in the context of the Olympic Games\\\".\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8039379884717232, \"rank\": 0.20653319090925995, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\", \"score\": 0.999999080847569, \"rank\": 9.191450081259641e-07, \"text\": \"Hedon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said she would look into \\\"the manner in which homeless people are sent outside of Paris to accommodation centres, the way in which living areas are being destroyed\\\".\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998954233488, \"rank\": 1.0457676216703239e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It posed the question of whether there was a policy \\\"of making undesirable people invisible\\\", she added.\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The investigation will also look into the use of student accommodation in Paris to house members of the emergency services and other State employees during the Games, which will mean around 2,000 students will have to be re-housed.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998954233488, \"rank\": 1.0457676216703239e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hedon will also probe restrictions placed on demonstrations, and the use of AI-assisted crowd monitoring software by the French police.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\", \"score\": 0.999999080847569, \"rank\": 9.191450081259641e-07, \"text\": \"Hedon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hedon\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0035799219579032e-21, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her findings are set to be published in April at the earliest.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Office for the Defence of Rights is an independent State institution, created in 2011, the role of which is to investigate possible rights abuses and make recommendations to the Government.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1429, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9992042311392761, \"rank\": 0.0006227485858531268, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Government has denied having a \\\"zero homeless\\\" target for the Olympics, saying that additional accommodation for rough sleepers would be part of the legacy of the Games.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1633, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9838352972003893, \"rank\": 0.01309474660152878, \"text\": \"French Government\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities in China cleared an unknown number of beggars, hawkers, and the homeless from the streets of China before the 2008 Beijing Olympics, with many shipped back to their home regions, reports said at the time.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9991299889875068, \"rank\": 0.0007494617215839603, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9991299889875068, \"rank\": 0.0007494617215839603, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazilian campaign groups also said Rio de Janeiro's homeless were forced out of tourist areas in the middle of the night as the city hosted the Games in 2016.\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics are set to run from July 26-August 11, followed by the Paralympics from August 28-September 8.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2316, \"entities\": []}]}"